1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with interference alignment, which is a topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the impact of CSI imperfection on the error performance of IA, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed adaptive transmission scheme can be seen as a control system that adapts to the uncertainty in CSI. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses bit loading algorithms that improve the error performance of IA, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus of the paper, the error performance of communication systems is relevant to cryptography and security.
